The paper deals with secure communication over a wiretap channel, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of joint learning and transmission schemes suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) component to the paper. The fact that the adversary has the ability to switch the channel state and observe the corresponding output at every channel use suggests a control systems (cs.SY) component. Finally, the use of adaptive strategies to learn and adapt to the adversary's actions suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) component.
